  "text": "Throughout this section we denote the Pólya-Aeppli and Poisson-exponential Lévy processes, which correspond to specific values of parameters µ ∈ R Since a generic compound Poisson-exponential Lévy process is a subordinator, it can be employed in lieu of the \"time\" argument to make a random time change. Therefore, one may consider a mixed Poisson process with time t replaced by a particular compound Poisson-exponential process. We refer to [CITATION_1] for more details on the mixed Poisson processes.",
